Package magellan.client.swing.tree

Interface SupportsEmphasizing

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AllianceNodeWrapper, BorderNodeWrapper, DefaultNodeWrapper, EmphasizingImpl, FactionNodeWrapper, GroupNodeWrapper, IslandNodeWrapper, ItemCategoryNodeWrapper, ItemNodeWrapper, MultiIconNodeWrapper, PotionNodeWrapper, RegionNodeWrapper, SimpleNodeWrapper, SkillNodeWrapper, SpellNodeWrapper, UnitCommentNodeWrapper, UnitContainerCommentNodeWrapper, UnitContainerNodeWrapper, UnitListNodeWrapper, UnitNodeWrapper, UnitRelationNodeWrapper, UnitRelationNodeWrapper2
    public interface SupportsEmphasizing
    An interface to be implemented by wrapper classes. Helps to create useful implementations of the emphasized method that is already defined in CellObject. The List that can be retrieved via getSubordinatedElements is supposed to contain those wrappers that are directly under the node that contains this wrapper. This List should be used to determine the return value of emphasized().
    Author:
    Ulrich Küster

      • getSubordinatedElements

        java.util.List<SupportsEmphasizing> getSubordinatedElements()
        Retrieve the subordinate elements of this wrapper. They are supposed to implement SupportsEmphasizing too. This way we can ask them and check whether all subordinated elements are not emphasized.
